text: Visit Actions
Demographics
Emergency Preparedness
Evacuation Location
Acuity Status
Disaster Status
Face-to-Face
Are there any comments on the patient's face-to-face visit?
codingInstructions: If it has already happened, say when. If it is scheduled to happen, describe when. If it is not scheduled yet, describe any conversations with patient about scheduling.
itemNotes: If a F2F is not already marked as received, the nurse needs to acknowledge that. Need to document something like "Spoke to patient and instructed they need a F2F in next few weeks." OR "Patient has a F2F scheduled on X date."

text: Personal
Primary Spoken Language
codingInstructions: If nothing is specifically mentioned, select "English"

text: Religion
codingInstructions: If nothing is specifically mentioned, select "Unknown"

text: Patient Goals
What was the patient's stated goal for home health care?
codingInstructions: This can be a sentence or sentence fragment - transcribe exactly what the nurse reported that the patient said.

text: Vital Signs & Measures
Vital Sign Parameters
Describe any adjustments needed to the default vital sign parameters.
processNotes: Do these get edited much? Can we prompt for any departure from default all at once?

text: Temperature
What was the patient's measured temperature, in degrees Fahrenheit?
Describe the method used to measure temperature.
Pulse
What was the patient's measured pulse rate, in bpm?
What type of pulse was measured?
Describe the pulse characteristics.
codingInstructions: If no mention of special characteristics is included, choose "WNL."

text: Respirations
What was the patient's measured respiration rate?
Describe the respiration characteristics.
codingInstructions: If no mention of special characteristics is included, choose "WNL."

text: Blood Pressure
What was the patient's blood pressure?
codingInstructions: Format the response as X/Y, where X is the systolic pressure and Y is the diasystolic pressure.

text: In what location was blood pressure measured?
In what position was the patient while blood pressure was measured?
Height
What is the patient's height?
codingInstructions: Format the response as X ft Y in.

text: Weight
What was the patient's measured weight, in pounds?
How was the patient's weight measured?
codingInstructions: If no direct comments are made about this, assume that scales were used.

text: Oxygen Saturation Level (%)
What was the patient's oxygen saturation level?
codingInstructions: Express the answer as a percent.

text: How many liters of oxygen is the patient on?
codingInstructions: If the patient is not on oxygen, select "on room air."

text: Additional Vital Signs
Which of the following additional vitals and measurements were taken during the start of care visit?
What was the patient's reported pain level?
codingInstructions: If no pain is reported, select 0.

text: What was the patient's blood sugar reading?
Was the blood sugar reading random or fasting?
What was the patient's measured INR level?
What was the patient's prothrombin time, in seconds?
What was the patient's ankle circumference, in centimeters?
Which ankle was measured to determine ankle circumference?
What was the patient's calf circumference, in centimeters?
Which calf was measured to determine calf circumference?
What was the patient's measured girth?
codingInstructions: Include units.

text: Interventions/Goals
Instruct patient/caregiver on signs/symptoms of disease that require immediate attention.
Was the intervention "Instruct patient / caregiver on signs / symptoms of disease that require immediate attention" provided during this visit?
Provide details about how the intervention "Instruct patient/caregiver on signs/symptoms of disease that require immediate attention" was provided.
codingInstructions: The response should closely resemble the template.
template: Instructed patien/caregiver on signs/symptoms of disease that require immediate attention.
